e Mott transition are not significantly detrimental to SC.\nThey rather suggest that repulsive electron interactions might even reinforce\nelecron-phonon SC, being then partly responsible for the large $T_{c}$ values,\nas proposed by theoretical models taking the electronic correlations as a key\ningredient.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Oct 2013 12:54:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Feb 2014 12:04:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 19 Feb 2014 09:28:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-02-20"}
